<br>
While the Proposed status system changes are a functional possibility, I must say I agree with Brandon, point for point. <br>
<br>
From what I understand, and I could be totally wrong on how this is supposed to work, the ideal Camarilla City is NEVER run by Neonates or usually even those as young as Ancillae. It would be the Elders who would hold the reigns and the system would be quite fudal/monarchic.<br>
<br>
That being said, the neonates would rarely be given much more than Acknowleged (and that would only come if the prince found that the new kindred was an asset and properly introduced/represented) unless they pulled off something monumental in the way of service to the city or one of the officers/primogen.<br>
<br>
