<br>
If so, then here's my two cents: I wouldn't mind at all if either the current or future staffs allowed Kirstin and John's proposals to be adopted. I recognize that it would be both a staff decision and a IC decision among those responsible for status. (Prince, Seneschal, Harpies, etc.) <br>
<br>
I feel this way for basically the reasons John expressed in his initial post. If a certain trait seems completely inappropriate for a character, I can't see myself role-playing it. I don't care if the status page says Character X should be &quot;Revered&quot;. If my character doesn't respect him that way, and if in fact few if any characters feel that way, then it simply doesn't work.   <br>
<br>
